  "text": "In order to assess the cardiac contractile state of the fixed ex vivo hearts, dimensions were compared to cardiac dimensions predicted by indexing to body mass [CITATION_1] in Table 3 . The interventricular septum wall thickness and left ventricle posterior wall thickness are approximately twice the predicted systolic wall thicknesses. The left ventricle cavity diameter is 5% greater than the predicted systolic left ventricle cavity diameter.",
